FBIS4-18050 "drsov083_b_94034" FBIS-SOV-94-083 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Yeltsin Orders Continued Study on Army Bases Abroad Yeltsin Orders Continued Study on Army Bases Abroad PM2904083194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 29 Apr 94 p 4 PM2904083194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Untitled Russian Federation president's Directive No. 184-rp, signed by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin and dated 10 April 1994] [Text] 1. The Russian Foreign Ministry, jointly with the Russian Defense Ministry and other interested ministries and departments of the Russian Federation, is to continue its work to study the possibilities of setting up Russian Federation Armed Forces military bases or military facilities on CIS states' territory by agreement with them. 2. This directive comes into force the moment it is signed. [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 10 April 1994
